WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.175
Myocarditis involves both innate and adaptive

00:00:03.175 --> 00:00:05.820
immune responses within the myocardium.

00:00:05.820 --> 00:00:08.995
An inciting trigger — most commonly

00:00:08.995 --> 00:00:12.169
viral — initiates direct myocyte injury,

00:00:12.169 --> 00:00:14.815
followed by immune cell infiltration.

00:00:14.815 --> 00:00:17.989
CD4 and CD8 T-lymphocytes, macrophages, and

00:00:17.989 --> 00:00:21.164
antibody-mediated mechanisms converge to produce myocyte

00:00:21.164 --> 00:00:23.809
necrosis, interstitial edema, and fibrosis.

00:00:23.809 --> 00:00:26.984
This inflammatory cascade is the root

00:00:26.984 --> 00:00:29.100
of its adverse sequelae.
